characteristics of the fortran cep language.wthe fortran cep languages differs from fortranii mainly because: () it extends the variety of the modes for real quantities; () it allows suitablemixtures, in an input/output list or in an expression, of quantities that occur under different modes; ()it makes it possible to address a greater number of input/output equipment; and () it removes the restrictionson the complexity of the list of quantities to be transmitted between the magnetic core memoryand the drum or the magnetic tape units.cacm july, mancino. o. g.ca jb march ,   : pm